caption: My favorite lil hideaway! Great food and friendly staff! The shrimp Spring Rolls are perfect and the Curry Chicken noodle soup has a great flavour with well balanced spicy/sweetness! (The perfect soup to fend off what ails you) ❤️ I love to grab lunch before shopping at the market next door to Dong Ky- it's the perfect Sunday!

This was my second time eating here within a week because I had to try the Pho I wasn't disappointed neither, I almost felt a Lil uncomfortable when I noticed I was being stared at while eating with chop sticks, We smiled it off though 😂🤣😂
Tasty and affordable Chinese and Vietnamese food. Don't let the interior decor scare you away (Order take out).

i used to work here. At the beginning, the owner promise to pay me 8.5$ per hour ( which is below minimum wage already). After work for 2 weeks, she just pay me 7$ per hour, when i asked her why she pay me the amount less than what she promise, she told me because i am a newbie!! Sound ridiculous!!!!!!

Favorite Pan fried rice noodles in the city.  Crunchy outside and soft chewy inside.  Looks small and unassuming being in a grocery store.  However I implore you to try this gem I found 12 years ago!  They have a wide assortment of condiments I was introduced to.  Especially the fried garlic.  They cemented my love of Vietnamese food.  The smoothies are also very delicious.  My favorite is avocado.
Best Vietnamese in Chicago. The Bun Bo Hue has to be the tastiest soup I've ever had.
Affordable and good portion size for lunch!
Great food and prices

Great little restaurant. I've been coming here for 20 years for the fresh spring rolls and the delicious pho. There is plenty of parking in an area where parking is impossible.  For those avoiding food chemicals: the fish sauce and dark colored sauces have loads of preservatives that can cause you head pressures. These are from bottles and the restaurant can't really be held accountable unless they choose to make their own natural sauce (which is what I hope they do in the future!)
(Translated by Google) Vegetarian noodle soup is very delicious, please remember to try it everyone  (Original) bún bò chay rất là ngon ghé nhớ thử nha mọi người

The pho isn’t very good but they have good fried rice. Food in general was a bit bland. Service was pretty good and prices were reasonable. All the workers wore masks. However, they didn’t try to social distance and when the “socially distanced” tables were full, they removed the signs from the tables that were not meant to seat people and let people sit there. I used quotation marks for socially distanced because even with the signs, the tables were not a minimum 6’ apart.
Flavourful and nice portions. Won't leave this place hungry. And they have an Asian grocery attached. Good place to get your food for the week.
I love this restaurant, me and my husband go here all the time. Delicious flavorful food, low key atmosphere it's a real gem. lovely people thank you
Always great food and service!

Bugs inside and the owner had my car towed when I went to the bank first. Even with receipt had to pay $225 to get my car back. Most expensive lunch ever. Don’t use their parking and better yet pay $5 to park and eat somewhere better.
This place can’t be beat. Awesome prices and food!
Authentic Vietnamese food  , also Chinese dishes,  soups are great Fried Shrimp is good.
Good food and prices.
You think you can find a better and cheaper bowl in Chicago? Phogetabout it
If you never had or like pho great place and the prices are decent
Great little Vietnamese restaurant. Delicious, well prepared food in a relaxed, comfortable and unpretentious environment. Efficient and friendly staff. This is a favourite place.
Definitely recommend the com suon and bun bo hue here. An authentic vietnamese restaurant. The che ba mau was good too but wasn't as good as the last time I got it (4 years ago)😬
It has bean at least 8 years since i eat here and i keep coming back. I really like the food, its not expensive and they have great service.

This is a hidden gem. Parking is abundant right in front of the restaurant. View is open and pleasant. Foods are vietnamese cuishine and authentic. I found some surprises on the menu and it reminds me a lot of my home country. Try the ones shown in  my pictures. They are dishes tasting lovely and fit the cold weather.
Very affordable, fresh food, friendly staff

Cheap prices but no ambience like eating at Walgreens...you're virtually sitting inside a grocery store.  Not that clean of a floor & tables are sticky.  Bathroom is dilapidated and their food is soso.
Cozy place. Friendly staff. Especially, you can order something that is not even on the menu. The chef will run to the market next door, buy super fresh ingredients and make it for you.

My go to spot for good Vietnamese food. They charge way less than the trendy spots.on argyle street that attract the dumb hipster crowds who recently "discovered" Vietnamese food. The service is good, staff is very friendly, portions are big and prices are amazing. A pork chop meal for 7.45 versus 11.00 on argyle street. Banh mi for $3.50 versus $6.95 on argyle street.
(Translated by Google) Efficient care kindness hygiene and delicious menu  (Original) Atención eficiente amabilidad higiene y delicioso menu
Reasonable price for very tasty foods
Definitely try the spring rolls, they are fabulous.

Best food at the best prices around. Vietnamese and Chinese menu with 120+ items. Decor style is "Hole in the wall" but the quality and consistency of the food more than make up for it. Staff is friendly and attentive.
Very fast, very fresh
This place tastes better and costs less than any other.
Their pho, fried rolls and some other plate w/ noodles, grilled pork, and a fried rolls w/ romaine lettuce is really good. But don't like that their floor is always slippery like it's greasy
Great place for quick bites before heading to the airport.
Excellent food and service. Byob.
Absolutely delicious
Been going here for years and the food is still awesome! Highly recommend the pork chop and egg foo young! Pho is really good too

If I had to say where my favorite place to get Pho and most of my Vietnamese dishes in Chicago, I would have to say Dong Ky! I have been going since I was in high school. I love the service and the staff. They are very friendly and if you go a few times they definitely recognize you. The pho has a ton of flavor even when you don't add the extra sauces and veggies. Their egg rolls, SPRING ROLLS, and crab rangoon are amazing as well. Their peanut sauce for the spring rolls is one of my favorites to get. I highly recommend trying this place out!
Love there spring Rolls 😍😍 😍
god soap

Dong Ky  offers good quality and very affordable food in a hole in the wall environment. The food is great for the price, if not the best you'll ever have, and the ambiance is basic but friendly.  Except for the pho, which comes in swimming pool size bowls, servings are on the ample size of reasonable.  The grocery store next door is a nice destination if you're inspired by the food and want traditional Asian ingredients.
The bun bu hue is the best I've ever had! Absurdly delicious and only $9.00 for a giant bowl. That's ridiculous. Go now, don't wait.
Great food and great prices.

Best food at the best prices around. Vietnamese and Chinese menu with 120+ items. Decor style is "Hole in the wall" but the quality and consistency of the food more than make up for it. Staff is friendly and attentive.
(Translated by Google) People are bustling a lot. I feel the distance from my taste. I feel a little salty in the food.  (Original) 사람들은 많이 북적댄다 내취향과는 거리가 느껴진다 음식들의 약간 짭게 느껴지는 편이다
Good soup!! Good service!!
This place is inside the convenience store, the staff was super friendly. Although the place doesn't look like much... I can tell you the food is certainly awesome...
Yum
They barely put any meat at all in pho quality went down
Good food..very fresh
Favorite little spot, don't crowd it up! Great flavor.
This place is family owned. They specialize in different soups but you can order other items as well. The dishes are not to hearty but the food is good.

Ok, not your place to go if you're squeamish about cleanliness or bad service :) but the asian food is great here.  some things are a hit and miss like the mi quang. i'm from houston which has excellent vietnamese food and my quest in chicago is to find something comparable. This place is pretty decent for pho or banh cuon. Like most other asian places the services is just ok and the place is not the cleanest, but if you're here for good and cheap eats then this is your place.  Update Oct.2018: We still frequent this spot in the neighborhood!  The staff is nice and more importantly, food is always consistent and fast! prices are good too. Bo Luc Lac is a must try, as well as the pork vermicelli bowl.  VN eggrolls are great too.

I am Japanese and love noodle with soup. But here noodle without soup is wonderfully delicious for me! I always order beef one with rice noodle, and then I put lots of diced garlic and some hot source at the table. They serve some fruit juices that my friend are falling love with. Once you park your car (watch out illegal parking. they tow immediately lol), you can enjoy your lunch here and shopping right next.

Love the Spring Rolls. Great House special beef Pho. Decent Orange chicken, lo meins, fried rice...BTW, its BYOB wine and beer. Enjoy the smoothies, too. Bathroom=C- Parking lot is great, but DO NOT leave the property. You will be towed in 1 minute!

A roach crawled on the wall behind me as I was eating today.  I was horrified. Nothing was done, except that the roach was killed with a napkin. They didn't even wash the wall after. I ended up losing my lunch in the parking lot. Disgusting. Do not eat here.
Nice place
We order their fresh summer rolls all the time from them.  They're a perfect party food.  Guests always love them.

username: Amando Respicio Boncales, BA, MSEd, MA PhDc

caption: Authentic vietnamese cuisine hidden within the borders of argyle. Servers may be crude and straightforward but the food speaks for itself.
Excellent food at a great price.  Not much for ambience but wonderful service!
Worst beef fried rice and orange chicken I have ever  tasted.

Staff was very nice and friendly. The thing I do not care for was the waitress after handing me the check stood over me, while I paid the bill. The Vietnamese pancake was ok it was too greasy/oily. The Vietnamese pork chop was bland, extremely small and on a giant plate of rice. I feel like the pork chop could have been bigger and cook more traditionally. The beef pho was good. The bathroom could be renovated. As the door handle was broken, toilet was running, and the water basin lid did not fit over correctly. The sink spout did not extend enough to wash your hands without hitting them on the sink. Will try other places.
small and not shining place but the taste is really Vietnamese tradition. I am Chinese but I do not go to China town to enjoy Vietnam noodle but I love here. Price is very cheap. I love spring rolls!
Ok food, lamentable service, in less than 5 min the asked what i wanted 3 times. Tbe menu is like reading a bible.
My go to place for authentic Vietnamese food. It is in a strip mall and not an attractive restaurant but food is good and cheap. Easy parking. Great staff.
for the price...it's the best food for your money
I just love this place. That's it, I love it. I could see people going and not liking it, but those people would not be my friends.
Good taste and good price
Poor service and very small portion!  Big bowl but not much in it.   Good for kids and elderly.
"Good food and very decent price".
Not so pricey compare to other Vietnamese restaurants
Great, inexpensive restaurant in a shopping center.  Had a vegetarian sandwich and is was the cheapest and most delicious thing I have had in Chicago.
AMAZINGLY DELICIOUS AND GOOD PRICING
Very good Pho. Excellent service
Their Mi Quang is amazing.
Really good food, good service. Try the egg rolls with the chili sauce... One Of The Best Vietnamese Restaurants I've had in Chicago...
Bug infest inside and when you tell the workers they just laugh
Prices used to be cheaper, but I guess they got more popular despite having the same dingy place with just decent Vietnamese food. Service is not good either.
Great bubble tea. Nice people. Cheap.
Excellent pho.
Good little noodle shop inside the grocery store
Standard Viet. Authentic for sure.
Very good pho...reasonably priced...located inside of the Asian supermarket in the shopping plaza
Not too good
This is real deal Vietnamese food. Fresh! Love the noodle soups. Atmosphere is a bit tacky, like a lot family run Asian restaurants, but clean. They happily cook to order. Very reasonably priced too.
My favorite place for Pho. Bowls are huge and oh-so-cheap, and greatly tasty. It's a no-frill type of place, but don't let that deter you. You won't be disappointed.

Dong Ky is a great value for traditional vietnamese eats, you simply cannot find a place around town that serves up good quality food at the prices that they do. I ordered their Pho soup, which is as good as any other of the pho places around Argyle, with fresh ingredients and a savory broth.

The Ca Kho To and Mi Xao Bo are on par with the dishes I'd had in Saigon while visiting.  The place isn't much to speak of, but the food is good. I haven't found a Ca Kho To as cheap and good as here in Chicago yet.

I love Dong Ky.  It's a no frills, good food, restaurant.  The prices are very low, and the portions are big.  I like the pho and the bun.  This is definitely a comfort food restaurant for me.  The smoothies are great too.  And there is always parking and an asian market in the same building.
Great food and service.  Tea excellent.

Cheap and delicious- in a strip mall, next to a nail place lies this little gem. I've never spent more than $15 and always come out super full, with tasty leftovers. Get their Banh Mi (any variety is great) and a noodle bowl. Make sure to ask for extra egg rolls in the bowl and to load up on their fish sauce.
This place might look hood but it the bomb. Food is cheap. Went there with the wife and 3kids came about $25 for like 6 different meals
